Following are the steps to debug source code in VS Code:
1. Install Required Extensions
2. Open your project
3. Set breakpoints
4. Configure launch setting
5. Start debugging-
  Click "Run and debug"
6. Debugging controls-
  Use the debugging controls in VS Code to navigate through the code:
      Step Over: Proceed to the next line of code.
      Step Into: Enter a function or method.
      Step Out: Finish the current function or method.
      Continue: Resume execution until the next breakpoint.
      Restart: Restart the debugging session.
      Stop: End the debugging session.
7. Debug Console
8. Fix issues
9. Terminate debugging-
  When you're done debugging, click the red square button in the Debug sidebar to stop the debugging session.
